**Summary of what the doc captures:**

- The issue claimed the leaderboard GET used round-level scoring (`getTournamentScoreRounds`), but the code was already correct — the issue was based on pre-work state
- `AGENTS.md`'s "Migrated from hole-by-hole to round-based scoring model" note describes a **data model** change (archive table), not an algorithm change — this caused the misdiagnosis
- The only `getTournamentScoreRounds` references are in audit tooling and test files; 0 matches exist in live API code
- Key code paths: `route.ts:149` → `rankEntriesWithHoles`, `route.ts:147` → `getTournamentHolesForGolfers`
- `tournament_holes` is the live scoring source; `tournament_score_rounds` is an archive written by cron but never read by GET
- Negative regression test at `route.test.ts:328` guards against round-level path reintroduction
