Written to `docs/solutions/issue-51.md`. 

Key finding: Issue #51 described a problem that was already fixed. The leaderboard GET endpoint at `route.ts:149` already calls `rankEntriesWithHoles` with `tournament_holes` data — not `getTournamentScoreRounds`. The issue author was looking at stale code state. The only remaining gap was README.md line 3 saying "round-by-round" instead of "hole-by-hole", which was corrected. The solution doc captures the wrong premise, the correct architecture (`tournament_holes` as source of truth, `tournament_score_rounds` as archive only), and the guard test at `route.test.ts:328` that prevents round-level path reintroduction.
